  "text": "Cowpea is known to be relatively drought tolerant [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ) and this attribute results in its cultivation mainly in the savanna and forest -savanna transitional zones of West Africa. Resource inputs in cowpea production are relatively low compared to those used in the production of other major staples, making its cultivation affordable by resource poor farmers [CITATION_3] ).",
